304. 




                     FREDERICK JOHN COTMAN (19)


                      to obliterating the crowing on a cheque for 28l. 10s. and uttering it; 


                     to forging an endorsement on an order for the payment of 28l. 10s. and uttering it; 


                     to stealing from a post-office letter-box a post letter and stealing out of it a cheque for 28l. 10s.; 


                     also to stealing from a post-office receiving-house 25 post letters, the property of 

                        Her Majesty's Postmaster-General; 


                     and to stealing out of a post letter a 5l. Bank of England note and one half-sovereign. 
                  The prisoner had formerly been in the service of the Post-office, and used his knowledge to commit these offences.—


                        Five Years' Penal Servitude.



                     [Pleaded guilty: see original trial image.]

MR. EDWARD CLARKE, Q.C., with 
MR. MCCOLL, Prosecuted; 
MR.
